sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the iShares MSCI Japan ETF ( EWJ ), where 42,600,000 units were destroyed, or a 3.2% decrease week over week.

And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the ProShares Ultra Consumer Goods ( UGE ), which lost 75,000 of its units, representing a 33.3% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
Among the largest underlying components of UGE, in morning trading today Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) is up about 0.2%, and Coca-Cola Company ( KO ) is lower by about 0.5%.
